ExceptionLogger - Class in com.radiotelescope.controller
System-wide component that will handle any exception experienced strictly within the radio telescope application (see 'basePackages') so the front-end can properly handle whenever an exception occurs. This will also log the exception so that admins can see that it occurred.

execute() - Method in class com.radiotelescope.contracts.role.Validate
Override of the Command.execute method that will validate the validateRequest method and if there are no errors, will update the class UserRole object and persist the changes, setting it to approved. As part of this, it will remove any pre-existing approved roles, as this role will replace any existing roles. It will create the class AccountActivateToken associated with the user. This excludes the base "user" role, as this just indicates that the user is logged in. This will also update the corresponding class AllottedTimeCap object for the role's default allotted time.

JWTAuthenticationFilter - Class in com.radiotelescope.security
Extension of the UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter that handles the JSON Web Token used to identify users. Acts as a wrapper around the login process that, upon successful authentication will create and return a JSON Web Token to the client.
JWTAuthenticationFilter(authenticationManager, jwtConfiguration) - Constructor for class com.radiotelescope.security.JWTAuthenticationFilter
Secondary constructor that takes an authentication manager object and sets the filter's authentication manager object to this parameter. It also takes a class JWTConfiguration object and sets the private variable to this.
JWTAuthorizationFilter - Class in com.radiotelescope.security
Extension of the BasicAuthenticationFilter that will grab JWT token from the request header and use it to grab the user's context from Spring Security. This will then be used to authenticate requests via role-based authentication
JWTAuthorizationFilter(authenticationManager, jwtConfiguration, userRepo) - Constructor for class com.radiotelescope.security.JWTAuthorizationFilter
Extension of the BasicAuthenticationFilter that will grab JWT token from the request header and use it to grab the user's context from Spring Security. This will then be used to authenticate requests via role-based authentication

loadUserByUsername(username) - Method in class com.radiotelescope.security.service.UserDetailsServiceImpl
Override of the UserDetailsService.loadUserByUsername used to load the user by the username (email) so it can create a class UserDetailsImpl object. It checks to make sure the email refers to a valid class User Entity. If it does not, (or the email is null) it will throw an error. It will then grab all of the user's roles and create the class UserDetailsImpl

require(requiredRoles, successCommand) - Method in class com.radiotelescope.security.FakeUserContext
Test implementation of the UserContext.require method. It will check the current roles against the required roles and if any are missing, this means validation has failed. In the event validation fails, we will return an class AccessReport data class containing a list of the missing roles. If validation succeeds, we will call the success command inside of the withAccess anonymous function parameter, which returns a class SimpleResult data class containing the success data type OR the failure data type
require(requiredRoles, successCommand) - Method in interface com.radiotelescope.security.UserContext
Abstract method declaration used when ALL roles in the UserRole.Role are required to pass validation
require(requiredRoles, successCommand) - Method in class com.radiotelescope.security.UserContextImpl
Override of the UserContext.require method that uses Spring Security to check if a user has all of the roles in the requiredRoles parameter. If they do, it will call the success command. If not, it will return the list of missing roles
requireAny(requiredRoles, successCommand) - Method in class com.radiotelescope.security.FakeUserContext
Test implementation of the UserContext.requireAny method. It will check the current roles against the required roles and if any of the required roles are found in the current roles list, then the user's action is allowed. Otherwise we will return an class AccessReport data class with a list of the missing roles
requireAny(requiredRoles, successCommand) - Method in interface com.radiotelescope.security.UserContext
Abstract method declaration used when any role in the UserRole.Role is sufficient for validation
requireAny(requiredRoles, successCommand) - Method in class com.radiotelescope.security.UserContextImpl
Override of the UserContext.requireAny method that uses Spring Security to check if a user has any of the roles in the requiredRoles parameter. If they do, it will call the success command. If not, it will return a list of the missing roles
